cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the analysis of medical images using a convolutional neural network (CNN) for computer-aided diagnosis applications. Specifically, it focuses on the fusion of multi-modality PET-CT images for detecting and segmenting lung cancer. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves medical imaging (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as it uses a CNN for feature fusion and image analysis.
